  "_narrative": "**Where We Stand**\nWe're tied for first in Pool C with everyone at 0 points, as the tournament is just getting underway. Rankings have us as the second-strongest team in the pool behind #3 Kincardine, but anything can happen in tournament hockey.\n\n**Our Next Game**\nWe face the Ennismore Eagles on Friday April 10 at 9:15 AM in our opening game. The rankings suggest we match up well against the #25 Eagles, but they'll come out hungry and fired up for Provincials.\n\n**Around the Pool**\nThe other 9:15 AM game has Kincardine taking on Windsor, which could set the early tone for pool standings. Later at 3:45 PM, we'll face Windsor while Ennismore battles Kincardine - those results will shape how tight this pool race becomes.",
  "_coaches_corner": {
    "don_cherry": "I'll tell ya, these Kanata Rangers girls are gonna show those Ennismore Eagles what heart and hustle look like! You kids out there, this is how the game grows - these young ladies are gonna battle hard and make us all proud!",
    "talking_points": "**First Game Energy** \u2014 This is our chance to set the tone for the entire tournament. We've prepared well and we're ready to show what Kanata Rangers hockey looks like when we execute our systems and support each other on every shift.\n\n**Discipline** \u2014 We've stayed clean so far and that discipline needs to carry into game action. Smart, physical play without taking unnecessary penalties will keep us on the attack and out of penalty trouble that can swing momentum.\n\n**The Opponent** \u2014 Ennismore is here for a reason and they'll be hungry to prove themselves against a higher-ranked team like us. Expect them to come out fast and physical, looking to catch us off-guard early, so we need to match their intensity from the opening faceoff.\n\n**What We Need** \u2014 Only pool winners advance, so every single point matters from game one. We want to start strong with two points today, but more importantly we need to play our complete 200-foot game and build the habits that will carry us through this tournament.",
